  "description": "Amendments to planning permission dated 16 May 2017 (RN: 16/07844/FULL) for Variation of condition 4 of planning permission dated 22 October 2015 (RN: 14/12787/FULL) for the Erection of a nine storey building (with basement and roof level plant) above and around the Bond Street eastern ticket hall Crossrail station box, for office (Class B1) and retail (Class A1) uses.  Demolition of rear wing of 20 Hanover Square and refurbishment and alteration for offices (Class B1) and restaurant/cafe (Class A3) uses.  Demolition and redevelopment of 72 New Bond Street and demolition and redevelopment behind retained street facades of 64-71 New Bond Street for retail (Class A1) and office (Class B1) uses, and six residential units (second to fourth floor) at Nos. 64-66.  Demolition and redevelopment of 18 Dering Street to provide service bay and plant.  Creation of a new public open space and public routes in the centre of the site. NAMELY, to amend the approved drawing numbers to allow the changes to the OSD and New Bond Street elevations, internal alterations to residential core, office passenger lifts, staff changing rooms and welfare facilities, vaults and retail layout; alterations to residential entrance lobby, introduction of residential roof terrace enclosures, alterations to office roof terraces and balustrades, provision of a mezzanine floor to the OSD retail unit, refinement of the OSD classing and realignment of the OSD colonnade gates introduction of louvres to energy centre and roof level plant enclosure; alterations to 20 Hanover Square, NAMELY, to vary wording of Condition 9 (Part 4) to read as follows 'allowance for potential future linkages to provide renewable heating to the Hanover Square Estate district heating system.'",
